Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary
    Interface Description
    Strategy
    This interface is used to define an abstraction for the strategy used to compute the analysis.
  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    AbstractDatabase
    This class is used to define an abstract implementation of the database functionalities so that the different variations of the databases may define their own specific instances of the local functions.
    AbstractViewer
    This class is used to define an abstract implementation of the viewer functionalities so that the different variations of the viewers may define their own specific instances of the local functions.
    AnalysisA
    This class is used to define an implementation of the strategy for computing the analysis.
    AnalysisB
    This class is used to define an implementation of the strategy for computing the analysis.

    AnalysisG
    This class is used to define an implementation of the strategy for computing the analysis.
    AnalysisH
    This class is used to define an implementation of the strategy for computing the analysis.
    AnalysisMap
    This class is used to define and host a hash map that defines each of the analysis types to an integer value so that the main UI is able to refer to each of these using a value from 1 to 8.
    Application
    This class is used as the main entry point to the application.
    ContextForAnalysis
    This class is used to create a specific instance of an analysis type based on the strategy design pattern working in conjunction with the analysis map.
    CountryMap
    This class is used to define and host a hash map that defines each of the country codes to the full country name so that the main UI is able to extract the country code using the full name.
    DataContainer
    This class defines a container that gets used for storing the data retrieved from the world bank as a year and value pair.
    ListOfViewers
    This class is used to create a list of viewers being chosen for the analysis.
    Login
    This class is used to create a login screen asking for user credentials and verifying them through the credentials database before being able to access the main UI features.
    MainUI
    This class is used to create and display the main UI for the application for the users to select the parameters needed for the analysis and visualize the data set back by the World-Bank.
    Model
    This class is used to store all the processed data retrieved from the World-Bank server and maintain the list of viewers accordingly.
    ProxyDatabase
    This class is used to define a middle man implementation of the abstract database functionalities for purposes of producing the Proxy design pattern.
    RealDatabase
    This class is used to define a middle man implementation of the abstract database functionalities for purposes of producing the Proxy design pattern.
    UserParameters
    This class is used to hold the user parameters that have been selected through the main UI window and hence store the analysis components needed by the World-Bank API.
    ViewerLine
    This class is used to design a Line Series viewer by extending and implementing a concrete design of the abstract viewer class.
    ViewerMap
    This class is used to define and host a hash map that defines each of the viewer types to a string value so that the main UI is able to refer to each of these using the drop-down menu strings.
    ViewerPie
    This class is used to design a Pie Chart viewer by extending and implementing a concrete design of the abstract viewer class.
    ViewerReport
    This class is used to design a Report viewer by extending and implementing a concrete design of the abstract viewer class.
    ViewerScatter
    This class is used to design a Scatter Plot viewer by extending and implementing a concrete design of the abstract viewer class.
    ViewerTime
    This class is used to design a Time Series viewer by extending and implementing a concrete design of the abstract viewer class.
    WorldBankAdapter
    This class is used to implement an adapter model for the World-Bank so that the application is able to interpret the JSON format of data being returned by the World-Bank API through HTTP GET requests.
    WorldBankInterface
    This class is used to implement a communication interface between the main application and the World-Bank database by employing the use of an adapter.
